'''Volkskas Beperk''' ({{lang-en|Peoples' Bank}}) was a [[South Africa]]n bank founded in 1934 as a [[Cooperative banking|cooperative loan bank]], becoming a [[commercial bank]] in 1941.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Last Trek: A Study of the Boer People and the Afrikaner Nation |last=Patterson |first=Sheila |page=165 |year=2004 |publisher=[[Routledge]] |isbn=978-0-415-32999-6 }}</ref> In 1991, by which time it had become South Africa's largest [[Afrikaner]] bank, Volkskas merged with [[United Building Society (South Africa)|United Building Society]], [[Allied Building Society (South Africa)|Allied Building Society]] and [[Trust Bank]] to form [[Absa Group Limited|Amalgamated Banks of South Africa]].<ref>{{cite news |title=From apartheid to mass appeal |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2005/may/10/southafrica.internationalnews |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=10 May 2005 |accessdate=14 March 2010 | location=London | first=Andrew | last=Meldrum}}</ref>

The bank issued [[banknote]]s for circulation in [[South West Africa]] between 1949 and 1959 from its [[Windhoek]] branch.{{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}

