== Requested move 3 March 2016 ==

<div class="boilerplate" style="background-color: #efe; margin: 2em 0 0 0; padding: 0 10px 0 10px; border: 1px dotted #aaa;"><!-- Template:RM top -->
:''The following is a closed discussion of a [[WP:requested moves|requested move]]. <span style="color:red">'''Please do not modify it.'''</span> Subsequent comments should be made in a new section on the talk page. Editors desiring to contest the closing decision should consider a [[Wikipedia:move review|move review]]. No further edits should be made to this section. ''

The result of the move request was: '''Not moved'''. Consensus is that the current names are correct per [[WP:CONSISTENCY]], <s>and [[WP:COMMONNAME]]</s>. {{rmnac}} &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;[[User:Amakuru|Amakuru]] ([[User talk:Amakuru|talk]]) 12:56, 11 March 2016 (UTC)
:<small>Closer's note: Following representation on my talk page, I have looked again at the arguments, and I find that the "WP:COMMONNAME" is not really satisfied - generally "first millennium" is more common than "1st millennium", so I have struck that from the close. However, the [[WP:CONSISTENCY]] policy still applies, and a consensus of those responding says that we should be consistent, so I am not re-opening the move request. &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;[[User:Amakuru|Amakuru]] ([[User talk:Amakuru|talk]]) 17:43, 14 March 2016 (UTC)</small>

----


* [[:1st millennium]] → {{no redirect|First millennium}}
* [[:2nd millennium]] → {{no redirect|Second millennium}}
* [[:3rd millennium]] → {{no redirect|Third millennium}}
* [[:4th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Fourth millennium}}
* [[:5th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Fifth millennium}}
* [[:6th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Sixth millennium}}
* [[:7th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Seventh millennium}}
* [[:8th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Eighth millennium}}
* [[:9th millennium]] → {{no redirect|Ninth millennium}}
* [[:1st century]] → {{no redirect|First century}}
* [[:2nd century]] → {{no redirect|Second century}}
* [[:3rd century]] → {{no redirect|Third century}}
* [[:4th century]] → {{no redirect|Fourth century}}
* [[:5th century]] → {{no redirect|Fifth century}}
* [[:6th century]] → {{no redirect|Sixth century}}
* [[:7th century]] → {{no redirect|Seventh century}}
* [[:8th century]] → {{no redirect|Eighth century}}
* [[:9th century]] → {{no redirect|Ninth century}}
– Per [[WP:MOS]], numbers from 1 to 10 are spelled in words, as said by [[User:Jdcrutch|Jdcrutch]]. [[User:GeoffreyT2000|GeoffreyT2000]] ([[User talk:GeoffreyT2000|talk]]) 23:18, 3 March 2016 (UTC)

*'''Support''':  I appreciate [[User:GeoffreyT2000|GeoffreyT2000]]'s requesting this move, which I support. [[User:Jdcrutch|<tt>''J.&nbsp;D.&nbsp;Crutchfield''</tt>]]&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;[[User_talk:Jdcrutch|Talk]] 23:27, 3 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' [[WP:IAR]] / [[WP:CONSISTENCY]] with other centuries ; other use numbers instead of worlds [[19th century]], [[16th century]], etc. There is no reason to make these different, since they are part of a set of articles. -- [[Special:Contributions/70.51.46.39|70.51.46.39]] ([[User talk:70.51.46.39|talk]]) 05:24, 4 March 2016 (UTC)
::'''Reply''':  The centuries listed by the anonymous IP address have numbers above nine.  This proposal applies only to those with numbers nine and lower.  [[User:Jdcrutch|<tt>''J.&nbsp;D.&nbsp;Crutchfield''</tt>]]&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;[[User_talk:Jdcrutch|Talk]] 17:17, 8 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' unless the millennia and centuries BC are included.
::'''Reply''':  As they should be.  [[User:Jdcrutch|<tt>''J.&nbsp;D.&nbsp;Crutchfield''</tt>]]&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;[[User_talk:Jdcrutch|Talk]] 18:06, 8 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' per Jdcrutch. If we did this, would we not also move years like [[3]] to years like [[Three]]? Even in formal writting, "3rd century" is very common over "Third century". '''[[User:Tahc|tahc]]''' '''<sup>[[User talk:Tahc|chat]]</sup>''' 18:25, 4 March 2016 (UTC)
::'''Reply''':  JDCrutch ''supports'' the proposal, so opposition is not "per JDCrutch".  We should indeed call the year Three "the year Three", though if we add an era to it, we can (but don't have to) write "the year 3 BCE", just as we would write "three gallons" but "3 gal."  [[User:Jdcrutch|<tt>''J.&nbsp;D.&nbsp;Crutchfield''</tt>]]&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;[[User_talk:Jdcrutch|Talk]] 21:20, 4 March 2016 (UTC)
:::His point is that per your argument we should do a bunch of utterly asinine moves from reasonable and concise current titles to titles that are really stupid (therefore we should ignore this guideline when it comes to century names). <span style="font-family:monospace;background:lightgrey;border:solid 1px;border-radius:5px;"> '''''[[User:Insertcleverphrasehere|InsertClever]][[Special:Contributions/Insertcleverphrasehere|Phrase]][[User talk:Insertcleverphrasehere|Here]]''''' </span> 20:01, 8 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' The numerical depiction is far more common. The [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style]] is getting too ridiculous for its minimal worth. [[User:Dimadick|Dimadick]] ([[User talk:Dimadick|talk]]) 19:16, 4 March 2016 (UTC)
::'''Reply''':  Far more common where?  Certainly not in the publishing world:  see the [http://www.apvschicago.com/2011/05/numbers-spell-out-or-use-numerals.html ''Chicago Manual of Style'' and Associated Press], the [http://www.bbc.co.uk/academy/journalism/article/art20130702112133541 BBC], the [http://www.amamanualofstyle.com/view/10.1093/jama/9780195176339.001.0001/med-9780195176339-div2-510 AMA], the [http://lcweb2.loc.gov/ammem/ndlpedit/handbook/numberdate.html Library of Congress], the [http://www.theguardian.com/guardian-observer-style-guide-n Guardian and Observer], and the [https://www.una.edu/writingcenter/docs/Writing-Resources/The%20Rules%20Regarding%20the%20Use%20Numerals%20in%20APA%20and%20MLA%20styles.pdf APA and MLA], to name but a few.
:::Google scholar does seem to indicate that "first century" is a lot more common than "1st century", [[https://scholar.google.co.nz/scholar?q=%22first+century%22+-%22twenty-first%22&btnG=&hl=en&as_sdt=0%2C5]], [[https://scholar.google.co.nz/scholar?hl=en&q=%221st+century%22&btnG=&as_sdt=1%2C5&as_sdtp=]]. I still like the consistency argument however. <span style="font-family:monospace;background:lightgrey;border:solid 1px;border-radius:5px;"> '''''[[User:Insertcleverphrasehere|InsertClever]][[Special:Contributions/Insertcleverphrasehere|Phrase]][[User talk:Insertcleverphrasehere|Here]]''''' </span> 20:10, 8 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' The numerical depiction is more common and more easily read. [[User:Pincrete|Pincrete]] ([[User talk:Pincrete|talk]]) 21:37, 6 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''', at some point you should try for some [[WP:CONSISTENCY]] and [[WP:ignore all rules]]. [[Wikipedia:You Can't Follow All The Rules, All The Time| You Can't Follow All The Rules, All The Time]]. <span style="font-family:monospace;background:lightgrey;border:solid 1px;border-radius:5px;"> '''''[[User:Insertcleverphrasehere|InsertClever]][[Special:Contributions/Insertcleverphrasehere|Phrase]][[User talk:Insertcleverphrasehere|Here]]''''' </span> 11:50, 7 March 2016 (UTC)
::Note that the rules seem to contradict each other. For example [[Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Dates_and_numbers#Centuries_and_millennia| This guideline]] seems to indicate that using numbers rather than words in exactly this situation is perfectly fine. <span style="font-family:monospace;background:lightgrey;border:solid 1px;border-radius:5px;"> '''''[[User:Insertcleverphrasehere|InsertClever]][[Special:Contributions/Insertcleverphrasehere|Phrase]][[User talk:Insertcleverphrasehere|Here]]''''' </span> 11:54, 7 March 2016 (UTC)

:::I corrected that error on 3 March, [[Wikipedia_talk:Manual_of_Style/Dates_and_numbers#Reconciling_.22Centuries_and_millennia.22_with_.22Numbers_as_figures_or_words.22|explaining my action on the talk page]], and the MOS now follows its own rule regarding numbers.  [[User:Jdcrutch|<tt>''J.&nbsp;D.&nbsp;Crutchfield''</tt>]]&nbsp;&#124;&nbsp;[[User_talk:Jdcrutch|Talk]] 18:06, 8 March 2016 (UTC)
::::If you wrote the guideline, then you have absolutely no business commenting on this move discussion. <span style="font-family:monospace;background:lightgrey;border:solid 1px;border-radius:5px;"> '''''[[User:Insertcleverphrasehere|InsertClever]][[Special:Contributions/Insertcleverphrasehere|Phrase]][[User talk:Insertcleverphrasehere|Here]]''''' </span> 19:58, 8 March 2016 (UTC)

*'''Support''' per nom and [[User:Insertcleverphrasehere]] ''[sic]''.  — [[User talk:AjaxSmack|<span style="border:1px solid #000073;background:#4D4DA6;padding:2px;color:#F9FFFF;text-shadow:black 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em"><font face="Georgia">&nbsp;'''AjaxSmack'''&nbsp;</font></span>]] 02:14, 9 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose''' These are [[Ordinal number (linguistics)|ordinal numbers]] not [[Cardinal number (linguistics)|cardinal numbers]] (integers), and ''temporal'' numbers don't fall under general usage in this way (does anyone actually write-out "ten AM" but draw the line at "11 AM"?). The nom, while otherwise making a good catch, is confusing the two types of numbers, and our [[WP:MOS]] should actually be clarified in all regards here rather than upending common usage. -- [[User:Kendrick7|Kendrick7]]<sup>[[User_talk:Kendrick7|talk]]</sup> 07:04, 10 March 2016 (UTC)
*'''Oppose'''. Kendrick7 says it very well, I can't add anything. [[User:Andrewa|Andrewa]] ([[User talk:Andrewa|talk]]) 04:48, 11 March 2016 (UTC)
----
