'''Netherton''' is a village and [[civil parish]] in the [[English county]] of [[Northumberland]]. The population of the village at the [[United Kingdom Census 2011|2011 census]] was 185.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neighbourhood.statistics.gov.uk/dissemination/LeadKeyFigures.do?a=7&b=11126849&c=NE65+7EP&d=16&e=62&g=6452791&i=1001x1003x1032x1004&m=0&r=0&s=1435747681008&enc=1|title=Parish population 2011|accessdate=1 July 2015}}</ref>

Located {{convert|6+1/2|mi}} northwest of the town of [[Rothbury]] Netherton is close to the [[Anglo-Scottish border]]. Historically it was part of the parish of [[Alwinton]] of which it formed the townships of '''Netherton Northside''' and '''Netherton Southside'''.<ref>[http://www.visionofbritain.org.uk/place/9518 Vision of Britain - Accessed: 20 November 2013]</ref> Also in the civil parish are the settlements of '''Netherton Burnfoot''' at {{gbmapping| NT995072}} and '''Burradon''' at {{gbmappingsmall|NT981061}}.
[[File:Star Inn, Netherton - geograph.org.uk - 306251.jpg|thumb|The Star Inn on 31 December 2006]]
The village's public house, the Star Inn, has its interior included in the National Inventory of Historic Pub Interiors by [[CAMRA]].<ref>[http://www.heritagepubs.org.uk/pubs/national-inventory-entry.asp?pubid=122 Campaign for Real Ale -  Accessed: 20 November 2013]</ref> It was listed in the first 40 editions of the CAMRA [[Good Beer Guide]] from 1974 until 2013, being one of only 7 pubs to achieve this.

There is a First School.<ref>[http://www.northumberland.schooljotter.com/netherton/ Netherton Northside First School - Accessed: 20 November 2013]</ref>

